result.name: Watami Japanese Casual Restaurant

reviews.text:
The price for the lunch set seemed reasonable so I gave it a try. I ordered the cold soba + California rolls. The set includes a drink.
After about 10 minutes that tray was given to me. No complain there cooking takes time. The soba seemed fresh but was tasteless. The taste of the rolls was OK but they were not strong enough and collapsed when taking them  with the chopsticks. 
I was given my drink after I finished all the food. 
The bill was an epic story. It took almost 15 min to have it set up. At some point, tired of waiting I had to go myself to the cashier to see why they still didn't returned my card. Two staff were there talking and laughing but not taking care of the bill.It is only after I talked to the manager that things went a bit faster. One could say it took long because the restaurant was full...Far from that it was not even half occupied, which should have warned me before I got in. At this time of the day it should have been full like all the restaurants around. 
Overall very very  disappointed.

Tried their breakfast this morning, you have to ordered before take a seat, then waitress will bring your meal to you. 

The price is not expensive and quality is good, +$3 then you can upgrade you noodles to 出前一丁 for western style breakfast. They also have Japanese style breakfasts, both are good. 

The service of waitresses are good and very polite. Kids are welcome, but your baby stroller need to park outside the restaurant.
They do offer cheap tea set with free flow of drinks.  Good to kill time in there.
Good Japanese meal at reasonable price
Good food, good service. Had the 2 person meal ($438) and it could feed a family of four, probably.

reviews.text:
完全唔夠人手，做事慢，部分員工態度差
食完份量少價錢貴我都算，炸物全部炸過龍，又乾又柴又難食

早餐味道一般，曾經試過等飲料超過45分鐘，中間催了超過兩次，飲料都不到

午餐味道不錯

The price for the lunch set seemed reasonable so I gave it a try. I ordered the cold soba + California rolls. The set includes a drink.
After about 10 minutes that tray was given to me. No complain there cooking takes time. The soba seemed fresh but was tasteless. The taste of the rolls was OK but they were not strong enough and collapsed when taking them  with the chopsticks. 
I was given my drink after I finished all the food. 
The bill was an epic story. It took almost 15 min to have it set up. At some point, tired of waiting I had to go myself to the cashier to see why they still didn't returned my card. Two staff were there talking and laughing but not taking care of the bill.It is only after I talked to the manager that things went a bit faster. One could say it took long because the restaurant was full...Far from that it was not even half occupied, which should have warned me before I got in. At this time of the day it should have been full like all the restaurants around. 
Overall very very  disappointed.
這間餐廳的價錢唔算貴，而食物質素都尚算可以接受， 平時已晚餐時間都要等位 ，如果鍾意食嘅可以早啲落去攞位
食物出品太咸令人很難接受，不過地方環境比較寬敞

reviews.text: Literally this made living in Tuen Mun better because of the easy air conditioned stop right at the end of the line... great place to kill time but for the love of heaven I wish there were more benches here to just sit... mission accomplished, Tuen Mun, I'm forced to wander and not abuse the free air conditioning

The location is very convenience where you can reach with MTR, buses, light rail, minibuses and cross border coaches. You can go to T-park with the coach.
There are different types of food you can choose but the price is relatively high. The shopping center is not large.
Nice place. For most important clean toilets, because it says a lot about the place. And I can tell you, it was super clean.

A typical shopping mall in hong kong targets mainland chinese, not a good place for locals or tourists who want some different from other malls. No rest place and super crowded, especially in weekends.
there is a Samsung Electronic company here with good service
